
<p>We have walked very pleasantly - Perhaps this is the point at which our paths diverge - then pass on singing Sue, and up the distant hill I journey on.<br><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">I have a Bird in spring</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Which for myself doth sing -</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">The spring decoys.</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">And as the summer nears -</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">And as the Rose appears,</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Robin is gone.</span><br><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Yet do I not repine</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Knowhing that Bird of mine</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Though flown -</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Learneth beyond the sea</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Melody new for me</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">And will return.</span><br><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Fast in safer hand</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Held in a truer Land</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Are min -</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">And though they now depart,</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Tell I my doubting heart</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">They're thine.</span><br><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">In a serener Bright,</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">In a more golden light</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">I see</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Each little doubt and fear,</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Each little discord here</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Removed.</span><br><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Then will I not repine,</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Knowing that Bird of mine</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Though flown</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Shall in distant tree</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Bright melody for me</span><br><span class="mw-poem-indented" style="display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;">Return.</span><br></p>
